devdoc.details: Multisig Wallet Smart Contract where multiple signatures/approvals  are needed for an outgoing transfer to take place. Anyone can deposit funds.  As soon as we want to spend funds, it requires the specified number of approvals.

approve(uint256).details: A method to approve a transfer by an owner.  It does the following:  Sets your approval for one of the transfer requests.  Updates the Transfer object.  Updates the mapping to record the approval for the msg.sender.  When the amount of approvals for a transfer has reached the limit, this function sends the transfer to the recipient.  An owner is no allowed to vote twice.  An owner is not allowed to vote on a tranfer request that has already been sent.

createTransfer(uint256,address).details: A method that creates an instance of the Transfer struct and push it into the  transferRequests array

deposit().details: A method to make a deposit.

getBalance().details: A method to get the sender's balance.

getTransferRequests().details: A method to get transfer requests information.

withdraw(uint256).details: A method to make a withdrawal only if there is sufficient balance.

  Updates the Transfer object.
  Updates the mapping to record the approval for the msg.sender.
  When the amount of approvals for a transfer has reached the limit, this function sends the transfer to the recipient.
  An owner is no allowed to vote twice.
